Introduction to Generics

Learning Objectives

Know what generics are
Understand when we would use generics
Understand how to make a simple generic class
Task

As an introduction to generics either:

watch the following video: Intro to Generics video

read generics.md in the generics directory

Answer the following questions:

What is one benefit of using generics in Java classes?

Generics allows the instances of a class to be more dynamic when created, the type
of a property in this class can be specified when creating an instance.

Name an example of a generic class that we have used in Java?



What is the syntax for declaring a generic class?

public class Generic<T> {

}

At what point does the generic type get specified?

When creating an instance of the class for testing or in a method.


Can generic types be of primitive type?

Yes, boolean , byte , char , short , int , long , float and double.

Can a generic class take more than one type parameters?

Yes.
